Trump calls off Pompeo's North Korea trip citing lack of progress on denuclearization<br />
<br />
President Donald Trump said Friday he asked Secretary of State Mike Pompeo to cancel a planned trip next week to North Korea, citing what he said was a lack of &quot;sufficient progress with respect to the denuclearization of the Korean Peninsula.&quot; Trump tied a future trip by Pompeo to progress in U.S.-China trade talks. Talks between U.S. and Chinese officials in Washington ended Thursday with no deal. Trump said on Twitter that he doesn't believe China is helping with denuclearization as they did in the past, &quot;because of our much tougher Trading stance.&quot;

